cs.LG, cs.FL, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.PL 

The paper proposes a novel algorithm for learning a B\"uchi automaton, which is a problem in machine learning and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of a formalism named family of DFAs (FDFAs), which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves classification trees, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also mentions the implementation of a library, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
